                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> annos XXX <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>NOS <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex cert="low">ocum</ex></expan> conparavit ΔϚI se et conp<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>ri suo <supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>IN <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> bene pauso iucundus NE<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>TPO<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="4"/>BE<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>M conparis meae memo<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>M F <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>BR</abbr><ex cert="low"/>IATET</expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex cert="low">anc</ex>ti</expan> viri ego vobisc<supplied reason="lost">um</supplied> secubo <lb n="6"/>Aurelia co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>i</abbr><ex>ux</ex></expan> SANSILO SVE feci COT<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>P<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>EIBI <lb n="7"/><supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied>BIERANO &amp;lt;H&amp;gt;<certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/>S |(decies centena milia)<certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex cert="low">ummum</ex></expan> et qui mecun <note>sic</note> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan> ELVEAGIV
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In der Spätantike sekundär als Rückseite eines Sarkophagkastens verwendet; gefunden in Wiederverwendung für einen Brunnen; in mehrere Teile gebrochen. Prokonnesischer Marmor. Oberfläche teils stark verrieben; teilweise weitere, nicht mehr identifizierbare Buchstabenreste erhalten. Hederae an Beginn und Ende von Z. 1-4. (B): Firatli; AE 1991: Leseabweichungen. Datierung: nach Feissel möglicherweise noch vorkonstantinisch.</p>
            </div>
